There are two aspects of state of a video session that is driven by traffic:
  - traffic state: OFF, ACTIVE, IDLE
  - psi state: UNKNOWN, GOOD, BAD
Other states are by configuration:
  - enabled


- A session's traffic state will be ACTIVE as soon as a packet is received.

- If no packets are received over a user-specified period of time, the session
will be in IDLE state.

- If no packets are received over an extended period of time (say 1 min),
the session will be in OFF state.


- A session's PSI state is UNKNOWN if no PSI has been snooped yet.

- If PSI snooping is completed and is acceptable, it will be in GOOD state.

- If the snooped PSI is not suitable for output, it will be in BAD state.
